This contract uses the OpenZeppelin contract Library to inherit functions from
Ownable.sol*
@notice createNewVault allows the contract owner to create a new WarpVault contract along with its associated Warp Wrapper Tokens*

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

params._WarpVault: is the address of the Warp Vault where the collateral is stored
params._amount: is the amount of LP being collateralized*
params._borrower: is the address of the borrower

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

checkCollateralValue(address,address).notice: checkCollateralValue is a view function that accepts an account address and an WarpVault contract address and returns the USD value of the collateral they have locked.

methods.constructor: the constructor function is fired during the contract deployment process. The constructor can only be fired once and is used to set up Oracle variables for the MoneyMarketFactory contract.

markAccountNonCompliant(address,address).notice: markAccountNonCompliant is used by a potential liquidator to mark an account as non compliant which starts its 30 minute timer
